________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

What happens if you create an Ingress without an Ingress Controller?

Answer: The Ingress object is created and stored in the cluster, but nothing routes traffic because there is no controller to process the Ingress rules.


Is an Ingress Controller part of Kubernetes by default?

Answer: No. Kubernetes provides the Ingress resource, but you must install an Ingress Controller (such as NGINX Ingress Controller or AWS Load Balancer Controller) to implement the routing rules.

